        "timestamp": "2019-03-27 10:58:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nwell, when infra is the time source, who synchronizes infra? or we assume we don't care, because more important is for get synchronization *throughout* the cluster?\nOf course when time servers are selected, infra is not the time authority, and the servers are potentially further away from cluster network, introducing latency, so so synchronization of nodes between themselves is less precise.",
        "patchset_number": 2
